n','','541-revision-3','','','2012-03-01 18:28:12','2012-03-01 18:28:12','',541,'/2012/03/541-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(557,1,'2012-02-29 20:39:49','2012-02-29 20:39:49','<p><strong><a class=\"contentlink\" href=\"mailto:rpaulino@sdlyons.com\" id=\"RobertPaulino\" name=\"RobertPaulino\">Robert J. Paulino</a></strong> is a Certified Forensic Locksmith and an ASE-Certified Automotive Technician with a unique combination of an extensive locksmithing background and a strong hands-on automotive background. Mr. Paulino has over 20 years&rsquo; experience in automotive and residential locksmithing and has over 25 years&rsquo; experience in automotive repair. He has extensive training in vehicle locking systems, electronic vehicle security systems, and vehicle fire origin and cause. Mr. Paulino is a court qualified expert in the field of automotive forensic analysis. He is widely respected for his expertise in forensic automotive locksmithing, vehicle collision repair evaluation, vehicle fire origin and cause, and mechanical systems analysis.</p>','Robert J. Paulino','','inherit','open','open','','549-revision-2','','','2012-02-29 20:39:49','2012-02-29 20:39:49','',549,'/2012/02/549-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(558,1,'2012-02-29 20:39:27','2012-02-29 20:39:27','<p><strong><a class=\"contentlink\" href=\"mailto:lpeck@sdlyons.com\" id=\"LouisPeck\" name=\"LouisPeck\">Louis R. Peck</a></strong> is a Mechanical Engineer (M.S.M.E.) and an Accident Reconstructionist. He received his Master of Science from the Worcester Polytechnic Institute in Worcester, Massachusetts, where his studies focused on impact mechanics, roadside safety, and predicting human injury in automotive collisions. Mr. Peck received his primary education in accident reconstruction from the Northwestern University in Chicago, Illinois, and receives continuing education at various universities and related associations around the country. He has also developed a nationally distributed software package for analyzing low-speed vehicular impacts, and has recently released a program to predict vehicle behavior during a utility pole impact. Mr. Peck is also trained in the latest Nikon Total Station mapping equipment and Vista FX accident reconstruction software.</p>','Louis R. Peck','','inherit','open','open','','547-revision-2','','','2012-02-29 20:39:27','2012-02-29 20:39:27','',547,'/2012/02/547-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(559,1,'2012-02-29 20:38:42','2012-02-29 20:38:42','<p><strong><a class=\"contentlink\" href=\"mailto:jsiegfried@sdlyons.com\" id=\"JamesSiegfried\" name=\"JamesSiegfried\">James Siegfried</a></strong> is a Mechanical Engineer (B.M.S.E.), receiving his primary education from the University of Rhode Island in Kingston, Rhode Island. He specializes in vehicle fire origin and cause and is a Certified Fire and Explosion Investigator (CFEI) and a Certified Vehicle Fire Investigator (CVFI), as certified through the National Association of Fire Investigators (NAFI). Mr. Siegfried has over 10 years experience examining, reviewing, and analyzing vehicular fires. In addition, he has extensive training and experience in analysis of vehicle mechanical failures, thefts, and anti-theft security devices. He receives continuing education and performs continuous research in the fields of fire origin and cause and mechanical and electronic vehicle security systems.</p>','James Siegfried','','inherit','open','open','','545-revision-2','','','2012-02-29 20:38:42','2012-02-29 20:38:42','',545,'/2012/02/545-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(560,1,'2012-02-29 20:34:16','2012-02-29 20:34:16','<p><strong><a class=\"contentlink\" href=\"mailto:dlyons@sdlyons.com\" id=\"DennisLyons\" name=\"DennisLyons\">Dennis Lyons</a></strong> is the founder and President of S. D. Lyons, Inc., and is an ASE Certified Master Automotive Technician, Master Auto Body and Paint Technician, and a Master Engine Machinist. He is also a Certified Forensic Locksmith, a Certified Fire and Explosion Investigator, and a Certified Vehicle Fire Investigator. He began his career in automotive accident reconstruction and vehicle forensics in 1978 with APC Engineering, which later became Avery Technical Services, located in Rhode Island. Mr. Lyons has over 25 years experience in electrical and mechanical failure analysis, vehicle fire origin and cause, and vehicle theft analysis. He is a court qualified expert in the areas of fire origin and cause, automotive ignition and security system analysis, mechanical failure analysis, and physical damage analysis. Mr. Lyons is a vehicle fire instructor at the Massachusetts Fire Academy and the Connecticut Fire Academy and has lectured around the country on the subjects of vehicle fire origin and cause and vehicle theft analysis.</p>\r\n','Dennis Lyons','','inherit','open','open','','543-revision-2','','','2012-02-29 20:34:16','2012-02-29 20:34:16','',543,'/2012/02/543-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(630,2,'2012-07-31 17:25:25','2012-07-31 17:25:25','<p><strong><a class=\"contentlink\" href=\"mailto:cborelli@sdlyons.com\" id=\"ChristopherBorelli\" name=\"ChristopherBorelli\">Christopher Borelli</a></strong> is a Mechanical Engineer (B.S.M.E.) and an ACTAR-accredited Accident Reconstructionist, and is the managing director of the Accident Reconstruction division of S. D. Lyons, Inc. Mr. Borelli received his primary education in accident reconstruction from the Northwestern University in Chicago, Illinois, and receives continuing education at various universities and related associations around the country. He has provided expert testimony for trials and arbitrations in Massachusetts, Rhode Island, and Connecticut. Mr. Borelli has over 14 years of experience reconstructing motor vehicle accidents. Test</p>\r\n','Christopher Borelli','Managing Director of AR','inherit','open','open','','541-autosave','','','2012-07-31 17:25:25','2012-07-31 17:25:25','',541,'http://www.accidentreview.com/2012/07/541-autosave/',0,'revision','